    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Arthur S. Moody was an American Methodist Episcopal clergyman.  He attended Syracuse 
		University, graduating in 1909, and served at Methodist Episcopal churches in several 
		New York State towns and villages.</p>
