    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Arthur S. Moody Papers</emph> consist primarily of correspondence, and relate entirely to Moody's pastorships and other activities with 
			the Methodist Episcopal Church.  New York churches represented include those of Plainville, West Winfield, 
			Homer, Lowville, Syracuse, and Geneva; there is also some correspondence with Syracuse University from Moody's
			student days.   The Geneva district correspondence includes church reports covering  the years 1927-1933, and there are also copies of Moody's "Country Parson" column written for 
        
        <emph render="italic">American Agriculturalist</emph>.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Material is arranged chronologically but sorted by organization, so there is some overlap 
			of time period in the various topics (for example, Syracuse University covers 1903-1909 while 
			the next subject, Plainville Parish, covers 1905-1906).</p>
    </arrangement>
